    <div class="cover-frame">
      <div class="cover-content">
        <div class="cover-mono">Buyer's Guide · Budget GBP · 2026</div>
        <div class="cover-title">Budget GBP <span style="opacity:0.6">·</span> Tools</div>
        <div class="cover-sub">10 Tested · Free → $49/mo · 90-day window</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="post-body-wrap">
    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">
        <p class="lede-p">"Budget GBP tool" means different things to different operators. <strong>Free</strong> (native GBP, Canva), <strong>cheap scheduler</strong> (Publer, OneUp, Circleboom), <strong>budget optimizer</strong> (Localo, Local Falcon), or <strong>done-for-you under $50</strong> (theStacc). Most budget round-ups mix all four — we ranked them by what they do for the price, not by the price alone.</p>

        <p>We tested 10 tools across the full budget spectrum over 90 days, across 5 single-location profiles. Here is the ranking by what you actually get under $100/mo — by hours saved, results moved, and the work each tool removes from your plate.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — Pick by budget tier</div>
          <p><strong>$0 stack:</strong> Native GBP + Canva Free + manual everything. <strong>Under $30/mo:</strong> Localo ($29) or Publer ($13) for scheduling. <strong>Under $50/mo:</strong> theStacc Local SEO ($49) — done-for-you. <strong>Under $100/mo:</strong> BrightLocal ($39) + Local Falcon ($25) for tracking + audits.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want done-for-you GBP for under $50?</h4>
            <p>theStacc handles posts, photos, review replies, and reporting. <strong>Local SEO at $49/mo</strong> — cheapest done-for-you tier on the market.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See a live demo <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No card · 15-min walkthrough</span>
